ext uri="{FF2B5EF4-FFF2-40B4-BE49-F238E27FC236}"><a16:creationId xmlns:a16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/main" id="{1C454308-975F-91CE-B6A6-913202728044}"/></a:ext></a:extLst></p:cNvPr><p:cNvPicPr><a:picLocks noChangeAspect="1"/></p:cNvPicPr><p:nvPr/></p:nvPicPr><p:blipFill><a:blip r:embed="rId11"/><a:stretch><a:fillRect/></a:stretch></p:blipFill><p:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="8248730" y="2943828"/><a:ext cx="329793" cy="329793"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"><a:avLst/></a:prstGeom></p:spPr></p:pic><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="6" name="Text 2"><a:extLst><a:ext uri="{FF2B5EF4-FFF2-40B4-BE49-F238E27FC236}"><a16:creationId xmlns:a16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/main" id="{848746B3-CD47-6AF9-1B47-1ECB74C56D51}"/></a:ext></a:extLst></p:cNvPr><p:cNvSpPr/><p:nvPr/></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="353257" y="3581270"/><a:ext cx="3530279" cy="2457946"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"><a:avLst/></a:prstGeom><a:noFill/><a:ln/></p:spPr><p:txBody><a:bodyPr wrap="square" rtlCol="0" anchor="t"/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr lvl="0"><a:lnSpc><a:spcPct val="150000"/></a:lnSpc><a:defRPr/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200" dirty="0"/><a:t>From pilot to full fleet without rebuilding. IntelliOps starts on Olive Garden's order flow and expands across all 11 brands and 2,100+ locations through the same platform. The AI layer handles increased transaction volume and parallel monitoring automatically — no new agents, no new licensing, no new timelines.</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr kumimoji="0" lang="en-US" sz="1200" b="0" i="0" u="none" strike="noStrike" kern="1200" cap="none" spc="0" normalizeH="0" baseline="0" noProof="0" dirty="0"><a:ln><a:noFill/></a:ln><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="000000"/></a:solidFill><a:effectLst/><a:uLnTx/><a:uFillTx/><a:latin typeface="GT Walsheim Light"/><a:ea typeface="+mn-ea"/><a:cs typeface="+mn-cs"/></a:endParaRPr></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="12" name="Text 2"><a:extLst><a:ext uri="{FF2B5EF4-FFF2-40B4-BE49-F238E27FC236}"><a16:creationId xmlns:a16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/main" id="{C207ECAA-F37D-DD24-A46B-95D86B3DDDD0}"/></a:ext></a:extLst></p:cNvPr><p:cNvSpPr/><p:nvPr/></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="4263499" y="3581270"/><a:ext cx="3530279" cy="2457946"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"><a:avLst/></a:prstGeom><a:noFill/><a:ln/></p:spPr><p:txBody><a:bodyPr wrap="square" rtlCol="0" anchor="t"/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr lvl="0"><a:lnSpc><a:spcPct val="150000"/></a:lnSpc><a:defRPr/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200" dirty="0"/><a:t>New journeys activate through configuration, not new projects. Adding a new feature — drive-through, third-party delivery, loyalty redemption — means authoring a new journey template, not provisioning new infrastructure. The same intelligence layer that monitors checkout today monitors any new guest interaction tomorrow.</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr kumimoji="0" lang="en-US" sz="1200" b="0" i="0" u="none" strike="noStrike" kern="1200" cap="none" spc="0" normalizeH="0" baseline="0" noProof="0" dirty="0"><a:ln><a:noFill/></a:ln><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="000000"/></a:solidFill><a:effectLst/><a:uLnTx/><a:uFillTx/><a:latin typeface="GT Walsheim Light"/><a:ea typeface="+mn-ea"/><a:cs typeface="+mn-cs"/></a:endParaRPr></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp><p:sp><p:nvSpPr><p:cNvPr id="14" name="Text 2"><a:extLst><a:ext uri="{FF2B5EF4-FFF2-40B4-BE49-F238E27FC236}"><a16:creationId xmlns:a16="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/drawing/2014/main" id="{9FDDBB08-46C9-427A-031F-F634833E0333}"/></a:ext></a:extLst></p:cNvPr><p:cNvSpPr/><p:nvPr/></p:nvSpPr><p:spPr><a:xfrm><a:off x="8194383" y="3581270"/><a:ext cx="3530279" cy="2457946"/></a:xfrm><a:prstGeom prst="rect"><a:avLst/></a:prstGeom><a:noFill/><a:ln/></p:spPr><p:txBody><a:bodyPr wrap="square" rtlCol="0" anchor="t"/><a:lstStyle/><a:p><a:pPr lvl="0"><a:lnSpc><a:spcPct val="150000"/></a:lnSpc><a:defRPr/></a:pPr><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" sz="1200" dirty="0"/><a:t>Platform licensing stays fixed as operational footprint grows. Agent licensing is per logical agent — not per location, transaction, or brand. As Darden scales from 10 pilot locations to full fleet, the platform cost does not move. Only infrastructure compute scales — and that is metered and controlled.</a:t></a:r><a:endParaRPr kumimoji="0" lang="en-US" sz="1200" b="0" i="0" u="none" strike="noStrike" kern="1200" cap="none" spc="0" normalizeH="0" baseline="0" noProof="0" dirty="0"><a:ln><a:noFill/></a:ln><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="000000"/></a:solidFill><a:effectLst/><a:uLnTx/><a:uFillTx/><a:latin typeface="GT Walsheim Light"/><a:ea typeface="+mn-ea"/><a:cs typeface="+mn-cs"/></a:endParaRPr></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp></p:spTree><p:extLst><p:ext uri="{BB962C8B-B14F-4D97-AF65-F5344CB8AC3E}"><p14:creationId xmlns:p14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/powerpoint/2010/main" val="1853762618"/></p:ext></p:extLst></p:cSld><p:clrMapOvr><a:masterClrMapping/></p:clrMapOvr><mc:AlternateContent xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" xmlns:p14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/powerpoint/2010/main"><mc:Choice Requires="p14"><p:transition spd="med" p14:dur="700"><p:fade/></p:transition></mc:Choice><mc:Fallback xmlns=""><p:transition spd="med"><p:fade/></p:transition></mc:Fallback></mc:AlternateContent></p:sld>